    "updated_at": "2025-06-12T00:02:41Z",
    "body": "Just realized this!\n\nCulprit is this: https://github.com/starship/starship/blob/d73771332865bc5adacbc540dac3e9aa4dc99f27/src/modules/sudo.rs#L21C1-L21C78\n\nUsing `sudo -n true` is a quick way to check if sudo is cached, but it generates a log entry on failure AND success.\nEven on an empty line.\n\nSuccess:\n```\nJun 11 19:46:42 runeterra sudo[409243]: pam_unix(sudo:session): session closed for user root\n```\nFailure:\n```\nJun 11 19:47:02 runeterra sudo[409884]:   carlos : a password is required ; TTY=pts/1 ; PWD=/home/carlos ; USER=root ; COMMAND=/usr/bin/true\n```\n\nThis is very noisy. Is there a better way of doing this? @matchai ",
